Compilation mode tracks entering and leaving of directories with messages in `GNU make' style.  This does not work when your `make' is internationalized.  There are workarounds:

* complex

{{{
(when (equal "ru_RU.UTF-8" (getenv "LANG"))
  ;; Automatically detecting entering/leaving directories in Russian
  (setf compilation-directory-matcher
	'("\\(?:вход в каталог\\|выход из каталог\\(а\\)\\) «\\(.+\\)»$" (2 . 1))))
}}}

* simple

{{{
M-x compile RET LANG=en_US.UTF-8 make RET
}}}

or even set LANG to English for Emacs

-- Аноним 2020-06-04 15:07 UTC

